# Role-Based Architecture Guide

## User Roles System

This application implements a three-tier role-based access control system:

### Core User Roles
- **admin**: Full system access, can manage all pentests, clients, and pentesters
- **pentester**: Limited to assigned pentests and vulnerability reporting
- **client**: View-only access to their own pentests and vulnerabilities

### Authentication Hook
Use [useUser hook](mdc:src/hooks/useUser.ts) for role-based logic:
```typescript
const { user, role, isAdmin, isPentester, isClient, loading } = useUser();

// Role checking methods
if (isAdmin()) { /* admin-only logic */ }
if (isPentester()) { /* pentester-only logic */ }
if (isClient()) { /* client-only logic */ }
```

### Conditional Rendering Pattern
Components should render different content based on user role:
```typescript
// Conditional API endpoints
const endpoint = isClient() 
  ? apiRoutes.client.pentests.details(id)
  : isPentester() 
    ? apiRoutes.pentester.pentestDetails(id)
    : apiRoutes.pentests.details(id);

// Conditional UI elements
{isAdmin() && <AdminOnlyComponent />}
{isPentester() && <PentesterFeatures />}
{isClient() && <ClientView />}
```

### Route Protection
- Use [RouteGuard component](mdc:src/components/auth/RouteGuard.tsx) for protecting routes
- All role-specific pages should be wrapped with appropriate guards
- Redirect unauthorized users to appropriate landing pages

### Key Components
- **Dashboard**: [Single dashboard](mdc:src/components/dashboard/Dashboard.tsx) with role-based content
- **Sidebar**: [Role-specific navigation](mdc:src/components/sidebar/Sidebar.tsx) 
- **Activities**: [Shared component](mdc:src/components/activePentests/subComponenets/Activities.tsx) with role-based API calls
